  "type": "feat",
  "name": "Intoxicating Petal Growth",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>Your sprouts reach deep into flesh, drawing out strength.</em></p><p><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.pf1-pow.feats.Item.tNhpgV2eEPrlPnOM]{Intoxicating Petal Style}, Knowledge (nature) 7 ranks</p><p><strong>Benefit</strong>: Whenever you inflict the sprout condition, you gain a number of temporary hit points equal to your initiation modifier plus the number of sprout stacks you inflicted. The temporary hit points last for one minute, or until they are lost, whichever is shorter. The temporary hit points granted by this effect stack up to a maximum of 50% of your maximum hit points, and each application resets the duration of all of these temporary hit points.</p><p>This ability can only trigger once per maneuver or ability, even if it inflicts sprout on multiple creatures.</p><p>Additionally, whenever a creature becomes inflicted by 10 or more total sprout stacks by you, they become completely subsumed by a cloak of flowers, vines, and leaves. They become entangled and treat all other creatures as if they have concealment. This effect is removed if the total sprout stacks you have inflicted on them is reduced below 10.</p>",
      "instructions": ""
    },
